--- In junit@yahoogroups.com, Shane Duan <sduan@b...> wrote:
> It looks that java executable is not found on your path.  I am not 
sure 
> which open tool you are using, but you need to check if there are 
anyway 
> for you to specify the path for java.exe in that open tool.
> 
> If not, you need to set your path environment variable to include 
the 
> path to java executable.  In windows, it is something like 
> "C:\j2sdk1.4.1_01\bin"
> 
> I would expect that this opentool is downloaded in a zip file and 
> majority of the time there is a README file telling you what you 
need to 
> do to make it work.
> 
> Thanks
> Shane
>
